Eric Harris fled from police in Tulsa, Oklahoma, on April 2 . 
  Deputies chased after him after he was allegedly caught trying to buy drugs and a gun from cops . 
  Robert Bates then yelled 'Taser! Taser!' but fired his gun instead of his Taser . 
  After firing one round into Harris, he says in shock: 'Oh, I shot him! I'm sorry' Video shows deputies chasing after him and tackling him to the ground . 
  Harris was later hospitalized but died an hour later . 
  Bates said he accidentally fired gun thinking he had Taser in hand . 
 